 Inventory Login Portal · v0.1

§ 01 · Introduction
1.1 · Purpose

This document provides a detailed description of the requirements for the Inventory Login Portal. It is intended for developers, testers, project managers, and stakeholders to understand system functionality, constraints, and expected behavior. It will also serve as a reference for system validation and future enhancements.

1.2 · Scope of the Product

Product name: Inventory Login Portal

What the product will do:
The Inventory Login Portal is a web-based interface that allows users to securely log in to an office inventory management system. It collects user credentials including email, password, and division, validates the inputs, and prepares authentication for accessing inventory-related features such as requesting items and managing stock.

What the product will NOT do:
The system will not handle full inventory management operations such as adding, updating, or deleting inventory items. It will not provide advanced authentication like biometric login or multi-factor authentication in the current version. It also does not include backend authentication or database integration in this phase.

Benefits / goals:
The system aims to simplify user access to the inventory platform, ensure basic validation of login credentials, and provide a clean, responsive user interface for better user experience.

Applicability:
This system is intended for office employees, administrators, and staff who need access to the inventory management system through a web browser.

